The paper deals with algorithms for computing maximum flow in directed planar graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and numerical analysis, which suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper may involve some combinatorial aspects, which could make cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a relevant sub-category as well.
